GovTrack website frontend

This repo contains the source code of the front-end for www.GovTrack.us.
The data-gathering scripts are elsewhere.

Installation
============

* Create a database make a settings_local.py based on settings_local.example.py.

* Install dependencies via OS package manager:

  apt-get install python-virtualenv python-lxml python-openid python-oauth2 \
     python-iso8601 python-numpy openjdk-7-jre
     
* Install additional dependencies into a virtualenv using `build/buildenv.sh`.
     
* For search, install elasticsearch:

  wget https://github.com/downloads/elasticsearch/elasticsearch/elasticsearch-0.19.8.deb
  dpkg -i elasticsearch-0.19.8.deb

* Initialize the database and check the site works.

  ./manage.py syncdb
  ./manage.py runserver
  
* Get the data files by running `build/rsync.sh` (run it from the main directory, rather than from within build).

* Load the data by running `./run_parsers.sh`

